  "text": "However, it remains unclear whether particular cholangiocarcinomas (e.g., small tumors) shed enough cfDNA to identify an alteration associated with cholangiocarcinoma. Of note, Wasenang et al. demonstrated that \"no significance difference in tumor size, stage, and survival time were observed between low and high methylation group\" [CITATION_1] .",
